President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation on November 7, 2019, recognizing Veterans Day and honoring the service, sacrifice, and contributions of American veterans. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of caring for and supporting veterans, highlighting the VA MISSION Act and increased funding for veterans' health services. It also addresses the issue of veteran suicide and the President's efforts to address this crisis through the President's Roadmap to Empower Veterans and End a National Tragedy of Suicide (PREVENTS). The proclamation calls on all Americans to recognize and honor veterans through public ceremonies, private thoughts, and prayers, and encourages the display of the U.S. flag and participation in patriotic activities.